dct_title_s: Territory of the United States from the Mississippi River to the Pacific Ocean : originally prepared to accompany the reports of the explorations for a Pacific railroad route : made in accordance with the 10th. and 11th. sections of the Army Appropriation, Act of March 3rd. 1853
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. At head of title: Head Quarters Corps of Engineers. War Department. Shows routes and dates of expeditions and surveys. Includes list of "Authorities" and inset "The territory of north western America ceded by Russia to the United States, 1868" (scale 1:9,000,000).
